<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Hypopygium</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Polypedilum (Cerobregma) huapingensis Liu &amp; Lin, sp. nov., holotype male A hypopygium, dorsal view B hypopygium, ventral view C abdomen D superior volsella E anal point. Scale bars: 100 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1011.59554.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/500137" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">4</figureCitation>
). Anal tergite with 46 median setae. Laterosternite IX with seven setae. Anal point as in Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Polypedilum (Cerobregma) huapingensis Liu &amp; Lin, sp. nov., holotype male A hypopygium, dorsal view B hypopygium, ventral view C abdomen D superior volsella E anal point. Scale bars: 100 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1011.59554.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/500137" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">4D</figureCitation>
, strong, contracted in middle, as a large inflated globe apically with a single candle-like spine, tapering, 143 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long. Transverse sternapodeme 93 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long; phallapodeme 168 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long. Gonocoxite 320 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long. Superior volsella 143 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long, with basal microtrichia and two inner setae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Polypedilum (Cerobregma) huapingensis Liu &amp; Lin, sp. nov., holotype male A hypopygium, dorsal view B hypopygium, ventral view C abdomen D superior volsella E anal point. Scale bars: 100 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1011.59554.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/500137" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">4E</figureCitation>
). Inferior volsella 164 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long, finger-shaped, divided into two lobes apically, with 24 long setae. Gonostylus 310 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
